  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Substituting <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span> for <span class=\"italic\">y</span> in the second equation gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 times, x squared, plus 6, equals, 2 times, open parenthesis, x plus 3, close parenthesis\"></span>. This equation can be solved as follows:<div class=\"tcp-03c15f24-799a-44a2-be34-df400508c3e3\"><table class=\"table_Borderless tcp-c425e124-3227-4af9-a2c7-652aeb085881\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"tcp-af3a9c03-4eb8-4c37-a5f8-e51ed84f3376\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x squared, plus 6, equals, 2 x plus 6\"></span></td><td class=\"tcp-5ad91201-6479-447c-99f8-e1b070cc9dc9\">Apply the distributive property.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"tcp-7d1d2c42-c52b-455a-aee9-f175160688c0\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x squared, plus 6, minus 2 x, minus 6, equals 0\"></span></td><td class=\"tcp-9c78c3d0-df94-453c-8065-266e563e9e80\">Subtract 2x and 6 from both sides of the equation.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"tcp-4e7eba3a-196e-4425-9f98-804573042022\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x squared, minus 2 x, equals 0\"></span></td><td class=\"tcp-d1031b08-e2ba-45a9-af31-cfb869f1f2ef\">Combine like terms.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"tcp-ef000b74-257c-4399-b576-122afdf9e904\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x times, open parenthesis, x minus 1, close parenthesis, equals 0\"></span></td><td class=\"tcp-d4bca920-a349-422d-9047-df707fdc8bc8\">Factor both terms on the left side of the equation<br>by 2x.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Thus, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 0\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 1\"></span> are the solutions to the system. Since <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x is greater than 0\"></span>, only <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 1\"></span> needs to be considered. The value of <span class=\"italic\">y</span> when <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 1\"></span> is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals x squared, which equals 1 squared, which equals 1\"></span>. Therefore, the value of <span class=\"italic\">xy</span> is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 times 1, equals 1\"></span>.</p><p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and likely result from a computational or conceptual error when solving this system of equations.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
